<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,474,1507]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,323,1374,1399]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This new species can be distinguished from its congeners by the eighth sternum with a strong thorn at middle on posterior margin in male; the signa crescented and slightly curved, with numerous toothlike spinules on outer surface in female.
</paragraph>
